"{\"uid\": \"wdam.com-2024-09-22-petal-police-cover-cruiser-special-olympics\", \"text\": \"PETAL, Miss. (WDAM) - A Petal police car got a makeover for a good cause.  The Petal Police Department held its first 'Cover the Cruiser' fundraiser Saturday to raise money for the Special Olympics' Law Enforcement Torch Run.  Anyone who donated to the department was given a sticker to write their name and place it on the cruiser.  The department said getting the community involved in its efforts to support the Special Olympics was the first step in raising awareness.  \\\"It's called 'Cover the Cruiser,'\\\" PPD Sergeant Aaron Jernigan said. \\\"We are just trying to get as many donations as we can for the Special Olympics. It just helps raise awareness for the Special Olympics. For those participating in it, all the participants and stuff like that.  \\\"It just helps make the event better for them whenever they go to participate.\\\"  The next Law Enforcement Torch Run and Special Olympics will be held in 2025.  Want more WDAM 7 news in your inbox? Clickhereto subscribe to our newsletter.  Copyright 2024 WDAM. All rights reserved.\"}"